subsection.def:
application
                    (申請) means an application to the Lands
                Tribunal under section 23(2) or 28(2);

claim
                    (申索) means a claim for compensation under
                    section 29;

claimant
                    (申索人) means a person who has made a claim for
                compensation;

paragraph.content:
a purchaser under an agreement for sale and purchase to whom the
                        benefit of an estate or interest referred to in paragraph (a) or (b) has
                        already passed;

subparagraph.content:
describe the land in, under or over which he proposes there may be created
                    an easement or other permanent or temporary right under section 15
                    and indicate the nature of that easement or right;

describe any land or building in respect of which he proposes he may
                    exercise the powers under section 19 and describe the general nature
                    of any operations which may be carried out;

paragraph.content:
state where and at what times a copy of the order and, where appropriate, a
                    plan of the land may be inspected in pursuance of subsection
                    (1)(c);

describe the land and the easement or right and state that an order
                    creating the easement or right has been made under section
                    15(1);

state where and at what times a copy of the order and a plan of the land
                    affected by the easement or right may be inspected in pursuance of subsection
                        (1)(c);

state that an order has been made under section 17(1) and
                    describe the area of the road, foreshore or sea-bed affected thereby and the
                    manner in which it will be affected;

state where and at what times a copy of the order and a plan of the
                    affected area of the road, foreshore or sea-bed may be inspected pursuant to
                    subsection (1)(c);

if there is no subsisting consent to the commencement of the building
                    works, withdraw any approval which he has or is deemed to have given to any
                    plan;

he advises, under subsection (4), that, for the time being, building works
                    on the land specified by him would be incompatible with the works or the use;
                    and

the claim being served on the Secretary within the appropriate period
                    specified in the fourth column of Part II of the Schedule;
                    and

in respect of a day on which the reference interest rate is published
                            (publication day)—is the reference interest rate;
                    and
